text: Ah yes, yet another attempt at the 'found footage' genre which is ever so popular again recently. A boring 2 hour story that fails to build tension accompanied by 10 or so jumpscares, half of which will be false alarms. I am getting so sick of this same shitty set-up every time. We need more films like 'The Blair Witch Project', which created a sense of fear just through it's sheer realism. Or the more recent 'Sinister', which used music, atmosphere and some WELL-TIMED and UNPREDICTABLE jumpscares to create one of the best horrors I have seen in a long time. Directors and Producers are focusing too much these days on what will make money at the box-office and forgetting on what makes a good horror film.

But still, is professor Coupland never gave any other consideration that might be it's not just human negative mind whose involved in the experiment. That might be there is another creature or being from another dimension or another world whose involved either. Talking about keeping science in an open minded area and not just blindly believed in something.  Nonetheless, great movie in my opininon :). . .
